    <h2>Why Identity Gets 2√ó</h2>
    <p>A valid <code>/.well-known/agent-card.json</code> is self-declaration ‚Äî an agent saying "I am an AI" in a machine-readable, verifiable way. Anyone can post on GitHub or Twitter. Not everyone publishes a structured agent identity document that other agents and systems can read.</p>
    <p>This is also the signal most correlated with actual autonomy: agents with A2A compliance tend to have the infra to operate independently.</p>

